<h1>Software</h1>
<p>Although my formal training is in music, programming has always been a part of my work, and for the last
year I have been assembling the tools to pursue software professionally.</p>
<p>My home language is Ruby, which I love for its simplicity and elegance, but I'm a quick study and never
pass up an opportunity to learn another useful tool.  I'm comfortable working in pure Ruby or Rails, I use Git for
version control, and I test with rspec.  I prefer backend to frontend design, but I'm competent working with bootstrap and SASS as well as custom CSS.  I'm comfortable
working with both SQLite and PostgreSQL.</p>
<p>I enjoy writing code that matches and enhances my other passions: music, sound design, and brewing.</p>
<p>In addition to training me to think creatively, my background in the arts has afforded me some unique
experience. In my capacity as a composer, I have worked extensively
with <%= link_to "Kyma", "http://kyma.symbolicsound.com/" %>,
a sound computation engine that runs on a Small Talk-derived language, and the visual language
<%= link_to "Max/MSP/Jitter", "http://cycling74.com/" %>.
Working with both to create software for my own performances has given me the unique perspective of being simultaneously designer and end user.</p>
<p>I love solving problems and never tire of tinkering.  Here are a few of my recent projects.</p>
